{#- Embedded C header — struct definition with named fields and function prototypes.

    This header generator follows eFMI semantics with the following constraints:
    - NO der() variables: rejection enforced at template render time (continuous derivatives forbidden)
    - ALLOWED: discrete state updates using pre(x): x_next = f(pre(x), u)
    - ALLOWED: continuous nonlinear functions: y = f(x, u) — evaluated, not integrated
    - NO built-in integrator: users specify sampling and any integration method
    - ALLOWED: discrete-valued logic (z, m) with pre() state tracking
    - All array dimensions statically determined at transpile time
    
    Generated struct holds states (x, z, m), inputs (u), parameters (p),
    constants, and algebraic variables (y, w). The init() function initializes
    all variables. The step(t, dt) function updates discrete states and re-evaluates
    algebraic outputs. No ODE solving; all dynamics must be discrete or instantaneous.
-#}
